Modifications by SwapDK add an optional `data` (raw hex calldata) and
`feeLimit` (SUN cap on energy) field to
`WalletAccountTron.sendTransaction` and `WalletAccountTron.signTransaction`.
When `data` is supplied, the wallet emits a `TriggerSmartContract`
transaction with the calldata verbatim (via tronweb's `input` option
on `transactionBuilder.triggerSmartContract` with an empty function
selector). Required for invoking the THORChain router's
`depositWithExpiry` for cross-chain swaps from TRON, since the upstream
public surface only exposes plain TRX transfers and hardcoded TRC-20
`transfer(address,uint256)`.

Specific modifications are noted in the changed files via header
comments. The intent is to upstream these changes — see the package
README for the PR tracking link.
